args: ...How long are you intending to hide?
Haw haw! That's a top-class seer for ya!
Haw haw! No need to be so on guard.\nWe just need your help with somethin'.
I assume I don't get to say no to this?
You're a right trig one, ain't ya?\nNow just follow me.
Sorry for makin' ya come all the way out\nhere. I assume ya knows who I am?
You are the boss of this backstreet area, \ncorrect? The one with a reputation for\nbeing an unscrupulous churl.
Haw! Everyone loves a good gossip,\nwhether the rumors they spread are\ntrue or not.
So what exactly do you want with me?
Ain't no need to be so tense! I just want\nya to do a little job for me.
Do you want me to tell you your fortune?
Nah, I got no interest in that. I just want\nya to tell me when someone who stands\nin my way is gonna die.
Sooner the better, by the way.
You seem to be misunderstanding the\nentire concept of fortune-telling.
What you need is a practitioner of curses.
Haw haw haw! Oh, there's no mistake.\nYou're the famous Deathbringer, after all.
H-how do you know that name?!
Haaaaw haw haw! Suspicious rumors are\nmy stock and trade, little lady!
N-no... I'll not tell a fortune like that\never again...
Hmm. Looks like it's time for me to\nstop playin' nice.
You ain't getting any say in this matter!\nI said DO IT, and yer GONNA DO IT!
I don't care if ya want to or not!
I knows how to make people do what I\nwant, so I do.
Bah. Looks like this is gonna get ugly.
Haw haw! Make her pay, boss!
Ah! You all came for me!
Been a long time, boss. I see yer just as\nmuch of a scumbag as ever.
Yer men are just havin' a little sleep—and\nunless ya wanna join 'em, maybe it's time\nya tried livin' an honest life.
That really the best line in yer arsenal?\nWhat a loser.
You aren't hurt, are you, Verica?
I'm perfectly fine. Thank you very much for\ncoming to my aid.
That musta been rough. Couldn't have\npicked a worse guy to tangle with.
No, this is all my fault at its root.\nIt was my sin that caused all of this.
This have somethin' to do with that\nDeathbringer dealie?
...Yes, that's right. People say that I bring\ndeath to those whose fortunes I tell.
Will you tell us what happened?
I suppose after involving you this much,\nI have a duty to do so.
Once, I believed that it was a mistake to\nfight against your destiny.
That was why I once peered into only the\nmost inevitable fate of all—one's death.
If what I told people made them sad,\nI could simply tell them that was their\nlot in life and feel nothing in my heart.
If they tried to beg me for help, I would\nsimply order them to stop resisting the\ninevitable.
But then, one day...I foretold the death of\nmy own younger brother.
I didn't know you had a younger brother.
He was still very young at the time, and\nthe thought that he would lose his life...\nit was just too cruel.
The moment I was faced with that reality,\nI realized the truth.
If people were to simply accept everything\nfortune-telling revealed as fate, then what\nwas the point in bothering to do it?
What purpose did my art even have?
No, it's not your fault. It's my own for not\nbeing able to win against fate.
But it was then that I resolved to stand up\nto the fates that my divination revealed.
So that's why you decided to help me?
That's correct. I still don't know whether\nfate's plan for you is good or ill, but I\nhave a duty to find out.
But do not fear. No matter how terrifying\nit may prove to be, I WILL defeat it.
I may have failed my brother, but that\nis all the more reason I cannot fail you!
Guh... I... I think I'm done for...\nSorry...everyone...
This is just like when I lost my brother...
Then is this fate, too? ...No.\nI will not allow it to happen!
